%ornaments fixture - pins the five <!...> ornament specials.
%Their staff[] byte codes were remapped out of the N-number range (230-250)
%so N18-N23 render as fret numbers; this fixture proves the ornaments still
%render. No N-numbers >=18, so ornament PS output is byte-identical to the
%upstream reference and this fixture is fully reference-comparable.
%half-cross/stroke/stroke# render in any style; the two mordents only draw
%under -b (baroque), so a baroque section follows the renaissance one.

b
0-a<!half-cross>
0-a<!stroke>
0-a<!stroke#>
b

-b

b
0-a<!half-cross>
0-a<!stroke>
0-a<!stroke#>
0-a<!2mordent>
0-a<!3mordent>
b
e
